After the electionsAfter the elections, Turkey started to gallop into an economic downfall.
According to Erdoğan Turkey was facing an “international economic war” and a “conspiracy of foreign forces”.
The combination of neoliberal policies and the influx of foreign capital generated a considerable amount of capital stock in Turkey.
As the Lira is now rapidly depreciating and the flow of foreign capital is running out, these mostly dollar-denominated debts are rising to unsustainable levels.
Their solutions and oursAll economic crisis of capitalism comes with a bill, with a price someone has to pay.